Jet spectra at $\sqrt{s} = 5.02$\TeV extrapolated from previous \pp measurements at $\sqrt{s} = 7$\TeV~\cite{Chatrchyan:2014gia}. Additional scaling factors listed in the legend are  applied to enhance the visibility. The horizontal bars represent the bin size, and the points are plotted in the center of the bin. The shaded boxes denote the systematic uncertainties in the extrapolation procedure. The statistical  uncertainties are smaller than the symbol size. }
